$(selector).action()
$("p").hide() hides all p
$(this).hide() hides current element
.prop() get current value from DOM
.attr() default value from HTML
$() returns a jQuery object (array-like wrapper obj)

.text() set/returns TEXT content of selected element $("btn1").text("abc") textchange beim btn
.html() set/returns the content of selected element
.val() set/returns the value of form fields
.attr()

-------ADD ELEMENTS
.append() .prepend() .after() .before() 
.remove() .empty() removes the childs

-------CSS Classes
.addClass()
.removeClass()
.toggleClass()
.css() $("p").css("background-color","yellow");

